values:
I just puked, I have not done so in like 3 years.  I guess thats what your body does when there are no more tears left to cry.  I cant sleep now, I have to be up in like 3 hours to get ready for work.  God I feel so sick right now, I think I will call into work tomorrow, though I was over an hour and a half late this last morning to work, they will have to deal with it, just like I have had to deal with my life and all the shit that it has handed me.


Just deal with it.

God, I am not a verry good friend, I just woke up Deana...
I am sorry.... I hope you have a good day, well, better then I will have....

-Joe

Oh God, I just want to die.....
*cries*
I will explain more tomorrow.....

-Joe

You know, I have a lot of news for you all out there in LJ land, but, right as this moment, I dont know if I feel like talking about it all.  So, I will tell you in due time, probably later on today when I get back up.  Just wanted you guys to know I am still alive....

-Joe

http://cgi.ebay.ca/ws/eBayISAPI.dll?ViewItem&item=2980180592

I auctally bid on this, can you beleave the price on it now?

AHAHAHA!

I... have you ever felt so confused, so upset, so not you that you feel like you just want to throw up?
I... have you ever felt so lost, not wanted, so misplaced that you just want to go to bed and never wake up again?
I... have you ever been so hurt by someone that you love dearly that you just want to run away and never look back?
I... have you ever sensed that the whole world is against you?
I... have you ever been so hurt that you just want to drive away into an oblivion?
I... have you ever been so upset, you felt as if you were drunk?
I... have you ever been so lost, that you know you will never find the way back home to where your heart is?
To where your life is?
To where you belong?
To where love lies?
I think I really pissed off Rachel, wich was the last thing I ever wanted to do.  I dont know what to do anymore.

I have to log off everything, my sister is going to be home here in a few hours.  I might not be around, I have to go back to work after visiting with my friends Nate and Chrissy.  So, here is what I am going to do.  You say you want to talk to her, here is your chance.  She is going to tell you that I wont be around for a bit, then just... I donno, talk to her.  Find out, if you want, and if you could for me, what the hell is going on with those pictures I found.  I dont know if I want to confront her about it, and dont bring up the fact that she prommised that she would never do it again.  That would just make her feel like total crap.  I dont know if she is in a really good mood, but yeah.  If you could do that for me, I would love you forever honey!

I love you as it is Rachel!
-Joe

Oh wow, I somehow jacked up my Journal, now how do I get all my text to be smaller?  AHHH!  This is so much more confusing then just normal HTML.

-Joe

Whelp, I am running a tad late as far as getting to work goes.  I just got up a little while ago, left Rachel a message on her cell phone, and called my friends and said I may not come over today.  I am not feeling the best today, but if I do feel better, I will come on over, however, I will give you a call ahead of time.  But for now everyone, I must go work my ass off for a couple of hours.  And no Rachel, it was not cute that I was still sleeping.  I fell asleep when doing laundry, so that is what I am waiting on now, so I have some form of clothing to go to work in, and when I woke up, it looked like I had been shot by a shotgun in the head.  All my hair was standing on end, just looks like my head about got blown off.  I look like shit this morning, errrr, afternoon that is.  Anyhow, everyone have a great day, and I will talk to you later tonight my angel!

 

Love ya Rachel!

-Joe

"Nobody understands love.  It seems to be Universal. Timeless. Yet, it's also very individual, filtered by our own lives and expectations. I don't understand love, and can't understand love, because it's a different thing for each of us."

Want you,
want you, you, you,
Doesn't matter that you're not here,
I forgive all the silences.

I want you,
I don't care,
I know you'll disappoint,
I'm a willing captive,
Why fight?
There's no point.

I want you,
Need to hold you in my arms,
Need to smell your sweat, inhale your breath,
That's where you belong,
That's where you were meant to be.

I want you, wherever you are,
I really don't care,
I just want you to be there.

I want to open your door,
Because I have my own key,
I want to come in,
Because you too, now want me.

I want you to need me,
I want to stare in your eyes,
I want your promises,
I don't care if they are lies.

I want your body,
Warm in my bed,
I want you near me,
I want you so bad.

<font face="Arial" size="2">I am just sitting here thinking to myself, Joe, is there anyone in this world for you?  Or Joe, have you had your one chance, and just missed it because it was torn away from you, ripped out of your arms by the one that you call God?"

Well, as you can tell, I am a tad depressed.  I dont know why, possibly because all of the stress that has been laid at the foot of my bed every morning I wake up.  Possibly the lady I live with is correct, maybe this is the bottom of the barrel, but what if the barrel goes deeper?  I mean, what if the barrel has no end in site, or even an end at all?

It seems as though every time I hit the bottom of the barrel, I get a helping hand, but only for a few feet.  The rest I have to do on my own I suppose, because that person that helps me out, is the same one that lets go of that very same rope that is suppose to help me out.

What if there is no end, and all I do is keep falling into this oblivious black barrel, how am I ever to get out?  I have almost nothing to go for in this episode called life.  Where am I to go if I have some place to go?  No one has told me, showed me, or even eluded that there is any place to go, but down.

It seems as if every time that it looks like the sun is going to shine for at least one full day, it doesnt.  The rain clouds come and engulf the sun and all its glory in a depressing haze of grays and black.  As I feel the stinging rain upon my face, I cant feel the tears streaming down my cheeks.  I dont know weather I am in a nightmare, or if this is what life is really like.  If I am dreaming, when will I ever wake up, when will I ever get the chance to smell the roses?  When will I ever get my break in life?

I dont know, maybe its all the pain I am in, the fear of the worst, or something other then that.  But all I know is that life is a depressing place to be.  I want to go dream, and wake up tomorrow to a sunny day, and a dream come true, though I know this will never happen.

May you forever not be like me.
Joe

<font face="Arial" size="2">Well, as a quick update, I have been kicked out of my dad's house, moved in with my friends that I am building a house for, and I am very sick.

Now, an elongated update.  About me being very sick, I have been visiting the hospital for the past 3 days, to get checked out for certain things that are wrong with me.  My symptoms are pain, passing blood instead of the other stuff, having to go every 30 min or so, and loss of appetite.  You may not want to hear this all, and seeing that I have not updated in a long ass time, I doubt that I have any readers.  However, if my friend C.B. reads this, thats all that matters.  Right now I am at my brothers house, awaiting tomorrow to come so that I can take the 15 min drive down to Iowa City, IA to go to the state hospital where I wont have to pay for anymore testing.  I have had blood work done, thats about it, and found that I am not anemic, and that my hemoglobin is way low.  Which, incase you dont know, means there is something seriously wrong with me.  They, from the start, have pointed their finger at colon cancer, or less severe pullops, but this kind of confirms it without going up there, which is why I am going to the state hospital tomorrow.

It seems that they are going to have to do a barium meal, and a colonoscopy.  Both are no fun I hear, but they need to be done.  So I am heading down there tomorrow to get one or them both done to me, and line myself up for more testing.  No fun.  It make take a month or so to find out for sure what is wrong, but they are going to be checking for pullops and cancer for sure first.

All in all, I am not scared, because I know that I will become better, no matter the prognosis, through the wonders of skilled doctors and/or chemicals.  The only thing that bothers me is that when I told my folks finally, my mom cried, my dad bawled, and my grandma broke down worse then a newborn.  I hate to see them cry over something about me.  I mean, I am not scared, so why should they be?  Anyhow, thats about it.

But last, I must apologize to Chrissy for not saying anything about this earlier, I really have not told many people about it, for the fact that I dont want to burden too many people with worry, and the fact that I dont like to talk about it much.

So that is all, and C.B. I will give you guys a call when I find your number, and tell you what is up.  I will also try to keep this updated as much as I can remember.  I hope I still can post a few things in here.

Love you all, those that read, and I will post more later after tomorrow.
-Joe

<font face="Arial" size="2">Well, I know its been a while, and prior to me going to work, I wanted to give everyone an update on how everything is going.  One word, not too well.  Well, I suppose that is three words, but who is counting anyways?

I want to make an apology for not entering in my journal like I use to, its all due to me working extensive, tough hours, and my body requiring me to sleep when I get home.  Thats all I do now is sleep, and work.  From time to time I miss eating the whole day, if I can remember to eat, or if I am not too tired, I will eat.

I am being removed from my fathers house, once again, only this time he has no reason to.  I have a job and am paying rent as he requires me to do.  Never been tardy, I have paid additional money if I feel like I have mooched more off him this month then last.  But whatever, its his house, and not mine.

Well, I must depart and go to work now, I am a little later then I wanted to be.

-Joe

I have become a part of a huge Radio Station that is online, GUNradio, and I have my own radio station that I brodcast at http://12.219.225.178:8000/listen.pls .  Check it out if you want, I take requests all the time, that is when I am online, and I play all sorts of music.  The station is usally online, besides then I am playing a game or watching a movie on my PC.  Please check it out, and tell me what you think of it!.

-Joe

For all of you that are reading this that isn't named Meredith, please take no notice of this entry.  If your name is Meredith, please take heed to this entry.

Ok, Meredith, if you are reading my Journal, I would like to know how in god's name did you ever get my address and why the hell are you reading it?  Listen, its over, don't think I will write anything in regards to how I wish we were back together because it just wont happen.  Im sorry, but it wont.  I wish that you would comprehend this and let the past stay in the past and don't try to bring our past into the now.  Understand?  I hope so.

-Joe

P.S.  I just wanted to say that you are a great girl and there is someone out there for you, its just not me ok?

As I sit here, after a long weekend of camping at my friend's Travis' house, I have come to the awareness of something that should have come to mind earlier in life.

You see, this whole weekend was spent with Travis, Jenny, Matt Keck, and Sunnie.  Travis and Jenny are engaged, and Sunnie and Matt have something going on between the two.  So, where is my girl?  Where do I fit in the equation?  I don't, I don't fit anywhere.  I am the odd ball.  The odd man out.

You see, I have realized that there is no place in this word for someone like me.  There is no special person for me.  Tonight Matt, Sunnie and I went to see Matt and Sunnie's friend Brandy.  Matt has a thing for Brandy and visa versa, and I have liked her since mid of middle school.  So it's a little odd being with them.

You see, we went there to play a little XboX and just hang out, all but that happened.  All that Sunnie, Brandy, and Matt wanted to do was spoon on Brandy's trampoline.  Where does Joe fit in?  Nowhere.  I just sat on the sidelines watching.

I have been going three years now without a real girlfriend.  I have picked the desperate ones, because that is all I can get, and really, that has all come to bite me in the ass in the long run.

So, I've been thinking that really, Rei was the only one for me and there will never be another one for me ever again.

I miss her so much.

-Joe

Here it is, finally Thursday the 15th!  You have no idea how excited I am!  I have been waiting for this day to come for over three years now!  You know what comes out tonight don't you?  THE MATRIX RELOADED!  YAHOO!  I cant wait!

Anyhow, thought you should know!

-Joe

Well, I am headed off to work now.  But before I go, I must say I am pissed off at my sister.  She has managed to really piss me off this time.  I have something to blackmale her with, which is something she does to me all the time, but she still thinks she can pull that 'tude with me all the time.  She acts all happy I am going to get kicked out.  I cant wait until I do leave so she can be hurt again because there will be no one there to sheild her from daddy's wrath.

So yeah, thats all I have to say, just had to get that off my chest.  And speeking of dad, I had a horrable dream last night.  I dont think I want to go into it though.  Yeah, its that bad.  Anyhow, ya'll have a good day!

-Joe

Wow, I was just looking at my moods and the music I listen to while typing these entries and I came to the conclusion that my mood matches the music that I am listening to at that present time.  Maybe music does impinge on your moods.  I don't know, perhaps its just coincidence.  Yeah, that's it, coincidence.

-Joe

Strategy for tonight : Pack for the moving date

Yes, I know, last night I should have not driven home.  But in all actuality, I was not THAT sloshed.  If there was someone that was departing the bar that prematurely, like I was, I would have caught a ride with them, but there wasn't.  Or even if it wasn't raining out, I would have walked to my mom's house and remained there until I was sober again.  Anyhow, it was a fine night all in all.  Only spending $10 and being pretty well off, you cant ask for too much of a better night.

Oh, and what is with this damn weather?  Its spring and its only like 40 out right now.  Make the cold go away, I want warmth!  Winter has depleted!  Gone!  Is no more!  Or at least should be!

-Joe


Strategy for today : Hit the computer sale in Des Moines

So, I went to the bar and am pretty hammered.  Its so cool to run into old people you knew back in High School.  Like this one guy that didn't like me back in HS,  Burgus(sp) Barr, bought me like three drinks for the one I purchased for him.  How cool is that?  Bear in mind the fact he didn't even like me back in HS.  Then another guy, I only know from him working at the local Maid-Rite, bought me like another five rounds of hard shots.  I mean, he didn't even know me for real, aside from the fact I worked there before he did, and that I only go in there for hot fudge shakes on a bi-daily basis.  So, I walked in there with my mind set at only spending about $30 on drinks, and I really only spent like $10, and ended up pretty hammered.  Pretty remarkable if you ask me.

Now I am not the one to promote driving under the influence, but yeah.  I drove myself home and was followed by a cop the whole way home.  But the funniest part about the whole thing is the reality that when I pulled on 3rd street, the main street that leads to mine, I pulled behind a police officer.  So, half way home from the bar I was followed by and following a cop.  And I must have been driving really well due to the fact that I didn't even get those stupid cherries flashed at me.

Man, I ran into a bunch of people I knew from back in HS.  It was uncanny.  I have altered my looks so much in the last three years that I wasn't positive if they would notice me.  Unusual inst it?  I thought so.

Anyhow, the ethical part of the story is don't drink and drive, because I don't indorse it at all!!!

-Joe


Strategy for today : Sleep and drink lots of water!

So, I came up with something to do tonight, seeing that I am all by myself, I decided I will go to the bars and see if I can convene with anyone I know.  Here it is 10, so I must disappear, I will write afterward, if I am not about to pass out.

-Joe

Strategy of tonight : Drink until drunk cant drunk no drinks
I am so bored, someone get online and chat with me or something please!

About me grilling.  I frequently grill for anywhere from six to the most was fifteen people about once every other week.  Its something I started to do to make me feel like I have friends.  Its , in a way, like alcohol, feels excellent until its all over, then you feel like crap still the next day.  Well, here I grill, and some people eat and run, others stick around for a fun game of Pictionary or pool, male versus female, or even to play my XboX and stupid fun games like 'Fusion Frenzy'.  All I ask in return is like a little money back, nothing too big you know, and or your friendship would be the best.  I suppose you cant buy friendship with food though.  I don't know.

-Joe

Strategy of today : Absolutely nothing, Mope around in a state of dejection

So yeah, I kicked the final two people out of my house at last.

Yeah, I grilled tonight for only 6 people, something I do a lot, I don't ask for a great deal in return besides treat me like a friend, rather then act like nothing.  Heck, I don't even ask for money, well, I indicate, obliquely, the fact that money would be a pleasant jester, but still, no one gets the clue I presume.  Anyhow, I will get into it further later on today when I am not so exhausted.  It doesn't sound like a huge deal, but you all will comprehend later.

I must send out a gigantic thank you to those of you that do read my journal, and I pledge I will catch up on yours as well.  Take care everyone, and sweet dreams.

-Joe
